A preliminary novelty search developed the following
U.S. Patents: 5,139,121; 5,752,748; 5,769,509; 5,800,025;
5,834,854; and 5,923,096.

According to one aspect of the present invention there is provided a motor vehicle comprising:
an electric powered brake system for braking road-engaging wheels of the motor vehicle;
an ignition switch for turning a motor of the motor vehicle on and off, including controlling the application of electric power to the electric powered brake system;
and a control for maintaining application of full electric power to the electric powered brake system when the ignition switch is operated from ON to OFF so long as at least one parameter of several parameters related to a respective component of the vehicle and indicative of a need to maintain full electric power application to the brake system continues to exist and for discontinuing application of full electric power to the brake system when all such parameters are indicative of lack of need to maintain full electric power application to the brake system characterised in that the control is effective to reduce the amount of electric power to the brake system when all such parameters are indicative of lack of need to maintain full electric power application to the brake system, and, at a later time, to discontinue the application of all electric power to the brake system provided that all such parameters have continued until the said later time to be indicative of lack of need to maintain full electric power application to the brake system.
